Comments/Issues: • wetland traversed for approx. 26 m • vegetation composition on the right-of-way is not consistent with what is observed immediately off right-of-way, however, the species observed are the appropriate succession species following clearings in a marsh • weeds and undesirable species found on pipeline right-of-way • no remedial efforts are recommended -  proper contours, moisture regime and seedbank were determined to be successfully reclaimed and wetland vegetation regeneration is anticipated to improve naturally over time• Site Record 1 (Appendix A)
